{
  "stem": "14060.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There was no-- look, by the time it came to '41, '42 Hungary was land-locked by all German occupied country-- Austria to the west, Slovakia to the north, Czechoslavakia, Yugoslavia to the south.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was a common border with Romania.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The Romanians, strangely enough, did not deport Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Even so, certain atrocities, like in Iasi, have happened.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But, of course, Romanians were always known that they are on the take.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And for some reason or other, the Romanian king didn't allow mass deportations which happened all around the countries.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this is basically my story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I could give you some minor anecdotes that, for instance, the Hungarian army commandeered all the bicycles for the army.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they took our bicycles away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Six months, nine months later, they gave us back a broken piece of bicycle.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You can imagine what sort of war they were fighting, the Hungarians, like bows and arrows, you know, on bicycles.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can give you another example.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They, they took all the horses in, in, in the outside villages and brought it in to a place and they took them to the army.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Just opposite was a big sort of a clearing, a park-- not a park, really, but trees and grass opposite the shul, the orthodox shul.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember it was this time of the year when there is late [NON-ENGLISH] and the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There's a time in between.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They wait for the [NON-ENGLISH] And I fell.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were chasing each other.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I fell down, and I hurt myself, so I had to have a tetanus injection.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I got it, and I got all blown up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And seemingly, it didn't agree with me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know, there are many childhood anecdotes which really have not a great deal to do with the war.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
